text:
two weeks ago today i kissed my kids goodbye & put my life in the hands of a higher power & a couple highly skilled surgeons. that day, i made myself & the universe a promise. if i came out alive i would accept my truths, shed my shame & own my past, no matter how uncomfortable it is. 
there are several reasons this shop means so much to me & why i place so much focus & attention on children impacted by abuse & trauma, my son being the number one reason & myself being the second. the thought of anything happening to our children is mostly likely the key architecture of hell but for some that fear is one dimensional, for me it is memories of childhood. like so so many wandering life silently suffering, i was the victim of abuse from a very early age until my teens and like most, iРђЎve lived my life believing it was my fault & i deserved it. i have allowed the tragic perpetual anger of others be my compass and constantly measured my worth by their broken scale. i never wanted this for my kids, i did everything in my power to prevent it. someone took that away from me with my son, another broken angry person gave him the inescapable nightmares & pain that i know so well.
child abuse is something no one wants to talk about because if we donРђЎt then it just doesnРђЎt exist.  some say, РђюtheyРђЎll grow out of it, eventually forget, right?РђЮ no!!, just because the abuse happens to a child and a bruise disappears, bones mend & that child eventually becomes an adult, doesnРђЎt mean the wounds are gone &  everything that happened just goes away. the emotional traumas are vast & for some, like myself, the physical repercussions of constant unrelenting abuse on the body can extend into adulthood. my surgery will not erase the years of suffering that led me there, it will not heal the many parts of myself that are still broken. what does go away and what aids in the healing process is the belief that victims arenРђЎt worthless, arenРђЎt at fault or any less deserving of love. we heal our world by not avoiding a topic because it makes some uncomfortable. we speak, & we speak loud.  so here i am, shedding my shame and showing you my scar that no child should ever grow up and own. ­ЪњЋ

text:
the american psychological association's hallucination-cum-epiphany that traditional masculinity is harmful to society proves that its members need their heads examined.  it's bewildering that they even contemplate, let alone express, this emotional reasoning, which runs counter to their mission of advancing psychology as a science.  i have a news flash for them: america became great thanks to traditional masculinity.  america is the home of the brave.

rather than science, the apa's twisted pronouncement reeks of sexist pathos and reflects a pessimistic political agenda.  it's just not good mental hygiene; in fact, labeling an entire group negatively is one of the cognitive distortions that cognitive behavioral therapy seeks to alleviate.  unless the apa is completely engulfed by the extremist elements of the #metoo movement subsumed by a toxic, anti-male vendetta, why would it descend into this mad morass?  it is repeating the mistakes of academia.

other cognitive distortions exhibited by the apa, such as emotional and motivated reasoning (generating arguments to corroborate a worldview), also pervade our college campuses.  the consequences are dreadful: confused and disoriented students who must tread carefully on trigger-warning eggshells scattered between safe zones.  ever vigilant lest they inadvertently offend a protected group's evolving sensibilities, many become mentally strained, even teetering on psychosis....РђЮ
-

selection week!  also known as Рђюyou canРђЎt polish a turdРђЮ
i was talking with a friend this week about how right now the men in my life are all examples of great men.  containers. maybe a little puzzled by us but still- great men. 
mind you, this is also the friend that since heРђЎs been around for a few turds of mine (and the aftermath) we have an agreement- he has to approve of someone coming into my life. 
this is also a friend that has absolute permission to call it like it is- thereРђЎs no sugar coating.  and then he said, Рђюyou havenРђЎt really been surrounded by many good men until now, have you?РђЮ yep.  having been in the world of active addiction and hiding it i chose the ones in active addiction, also hiding things.  you know what else active addicts do?  they lie.  and cheat.  and go where the wind blows. 
so what changed? 
it wasnРђЎt wanting something
it wasnРђЎt loa meditations
it wasnРђЎt more yoga or green juice 
healing.  getting to the root cause behind what i was hiding and pretending.  and the parade of turds disappeared. 
if i can do it.....

text:
i was 11-12 years old when r.kellyРђЎs music entered my life. i adored, admired and was a huge fan of him. i had the cds. the lyrics to every album memorized. 
in 1995 (i was 14) his album r.kelly came out (with down low) and song number 6 became me and my first boyfriends song. i can still sing every word. 
r.kelly is a musical genius with a disturbing private life. his voice was soulful, real, smooth and sexy. 
during this time he had been charged with child pornography. i didnРђЎt believe it. it was before cell phone cameras etc so no proof besides a tape that he said wasnРђЎt him. 
we blocked it. the fans blocked the man he really was. i was as young as the girls he was manipulating, abusing and controlling. 
i felt sick watching surviving r.kelly, he got away with soooo much right in front of everyoneРђЎs faces! 
but he was successful, a collaborator, a money maker...no label would drop that paycheck. 
honestly, if i were at a party at 15 years old and he was there taking notice, i may have done what he said too. the brainwashing of impressionable girls is sad and sickening. 
fans loved him, believed him. not guilty charge means he didnРђЎt do it right? wrong. he won that bc the victim in the video did not come forward...because she is still trapped by him to this day. 
this man continued to drop music, told us if we believed it, we could fly. he put prayer and god into his music, to help that stained image. guess what? it worked. we all still loved him. 
do you suppose if these girls were white he would have gotten away with it?? i doubt it. these were women too, he prayed on them. victimized them. this is what we call a РђюpredatorРђЮ. so iРђЎm saying this today, for me and all women!! #muterkelly 
these brave women have spoken out, heРђЎs destroyed many lives. i stand with these women and all women who have been manipulated, abused and brainwashed by a man. 
#metoo #women #brave #whiteorblack #unite #timesup #brainwashamerica #sad #empowerwomen #toleave

text:
breaking news: detroit free press

it has been approximately 3 years, 8 months, and 14 days since my domestic abuse tragedy with my ex husband, former senator virgil smith.

today, i share my unapologetic truth with you, in all transparency. my hope is that the person reading this now who may be a survivor or currently a victim of intimate partner violence becomes empowered.

empowered to make a change and put themselves first, brave enough to use their voice, and compelled to love themselves endlessly. 
i specifically shared my story highlighting that domestic violence happens to the high powered ceo that you read about and see in our communities,or the mate of a high powered community figure who have, and are currently- suffering in silence. i know many...@detroitfreepress 
#thepurpleprint #detroitfreepress #virgilsmith #senatorvirgilsmith #domesticabuse #domesticviolence #believeblackwomen #metoo #surviving #womeninpower #women #blackwomen

text:
#thursdaythoughts ­ЪњГ... with the latest annual golden globes came a new wave of support for the #metoo and timesup movement. in the past two years, a global surge of support against sexual harassment and assault has risen, sparking accusations against powerful men in a variety of industries. the revolutionary anti-sexual assault and womenРђЎs empowerment movements have opened up public conversation about womenРђЎs issues around the world. 
#metoo is about giving people a voice. the movement has encouraged numerous women to speak out about sexual violence and harassment. the #metoo website describes their motto as Рђюempowerment through empathy,РђЮ which is a crucial message to resonate amongst survivors of abuse, to show that they are not alone. it has created a solid sisterhood, connecting strong women together, fuelling each otherРђЎs confidence. in addition to #metoo, the timesup organisation focuses on bringing safety, fairness and dignified work to working women; an endured issues that is strongly prevalent throughout many industries today. 
we do not want more, we just want equality; it sounds simple enough, but we would not have movements such as #metoo and timesup if it was that easy. 
but the creation of such movements have begun a widespread protest for change which has made an irreversible impact.  it has allowed for women to never return to the days of shame or isolation. and we believe that it is beginning to serve as a catalyst for women everywhere to stand firm in the face of adversity. 
we are living in a time where women are still fighting for basic fairness. the campaigns which we speak of encourage resilience and bravery. although it is shocking to say that in this current climate we are still fighting against issues morally incorrect, it only defines the purpose for our voices even more. ultimately, #metoo and timesup have not only added to the rights of women but have served as a safeguard for many. the unfortunate factor that we still have to battle for our safety sounds ridiculous but it is a reality that we will no longer avoid. we must continue to make it our priority to see change in equity, safety, parity and inclusion, however small it is.

text:
­ЪЊЌ k├цrlekens antarktis (love's antarctica) by sara stridsberg (2018) ­ЪЊЌ
.
­ЪЎј ­ЪЎј ­ЪЎј ­ЪЎј/5
.
in this book ninni, a brutally murdered woman, remember her life and murder. it is a tough life where ninni ends up using drugs, involved in prostitution and losing custody of her two children. the book is brutal and detailed in its descriptions, divided into short chapters.
stridsberg writes beautifully and creates an intense atmosphere without the story being a crime/thriller. ninni tells her story directly to you as a reader and the murderer is almost completely uninteresting. the murderer is just yet another man that hates women. one of the things that i found really haunting was the concept that you die three times: first when your heart stops beating, next when your remains are put to rest and finally the last time somebody says your name. until then you are present in the world but not able to interact with anything. considering the way society exposes murdered women this last death struck me as awful. the book made me look more closely on my love for crime in podcasts and books, i still haven't come to a conclusion so i will continue debating with myself. i also thought a lot about who gets to tell the stories of people who are at a disadvantage, how the view of women in prostitution is often simplified and used by other people to drive their own agenda. one of the best things with #metoo in sweden is that women with experience of prostitution did their own #metoo statement (the same as women of several industries like law, health care, it). now that their voices have been allowed to be heard they have raised so many important points and i'm in awe of their bravery.
.

­ЪЊЌ k├цrlekens antarktis (love's antarctica) by sara stridsberg (2018) ­ЪЊЌ
.
­ЪЎј ­ЪЎј ­ЪЎј ­ЪЎј/5
.
in this book ninni, a brutally murdered woman, remember her life and murder. it is a tough life where ninni ends up using drugs, involved in prostitution and losing custody of her two children. the book is brutal and detailed in its descriptions, divided into short chapters.
stridsberg writes beautifully and creates an intense atmosphere without the story being a crime/thriller. ninni tells her story directly to you as a reader and the murderer is almost completely uninteresting. the murderer is just yet another man that hates women. one of the things that i found really haunting was the concept that you die three times: first when your heart stops beating, next when your remains are put to rest and finally the last time somebody says your name. until then you are present in the world but not able to interact with anything. considering the way society exposes murdered women this last death struck me as awful. the book made me look more closely on my love for crime in podcasts and books, i still have not come to a conclusion so i will continue debating with myself. i also thought a lot about who gets to tell the stories of people who are at a disadvantage, how the view of women in prostitution is often simplified and used by other people to drive their own agenda. one of the best things with #metoo in sweden is that women with experience of prostitution did their own #metoo statement (the same as women of several industries like law, health care, it). now that their voices have been allowed to be heard they have raised so many important points and i am in awe of their bravery.
.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateРёб was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
a poem (2001) from my forthcoming memoir, "emerald rising"... photography: mair prudence 2019

journey into self

my life is a surrealistic 
matrix.
i have stumbled and fallen 
and slipped through the 
looking glass.
there is no wonderland, 
only darkness
which shrouds my existence.
as i peer through
the transparent glass curtain 
to view where i have been, 
i find 
i cannot retrogressively 
penetrate.
they don't see me. 
they don't hear me. 
i lay in shiver...
a voyeur.
life goes on as if a 
movie.
there is no escape
ultimately leaving no choice
but to 
explore.
am i to turn away from that
world?!
i hear you,  but i am 
frightened.
"i know.
now..."

text:
fancy a drink love? ­ЪЇИyou are under no obligation to accept drinks from strangers
­ЪЇИit is not rude or ungrateful to politely decline
­ЪЇИif you are uncomfortable you are allowed to just walk away
­ЪЇИyou do not have to justify saying no
­ЪЇИif you accept a drink you have not signed up to anything more than taking that drink

text:
it seems pretty fashionable lately to talk about #trauma whether or not you have it, so here are a myriad of thoughts i have on this subject. (tw: sexual violence)
РЮц№ИЈ
1. i didnРђЎt ever receive effective help until i began trauma-informed counseling at #hopeworks of howard county, and i tried all kinds of therapists and healers before this. you do not have to be a howard county resident to receive services. cost is not a barrier here. they are mostly a center for sexual violence but they have all kinds of sister programs and legal help. call 410 997 0304 to find out more about their services or speak to someone. РЮц№ИЈ2. there are many well-intentioned people in this world that do. not. understand. trauma. this includes friends, family, and even licensed therapists. you are not obligated to tell anyone your story. part of consent is boundary-setting with your own truth. just because someone wants to help you does not mean they have the capacity to do so. 
while the #metoo movement was #empowering and a sign that things were moving in the right direction, it has created a culture of trauma sharing as a form of social capital. Рђюsafe spaceРђЮ is thrown around casually. and sharing your trauma doesnРђЎt mean that you will be any more protected, or that any action will change. [throwback to the time a member of my troupe confessed their history of predatory behavior to me, threatened to rape me, and was still permitted to attend social events involving fire manipulation. the troupe was told that lies and rumors made me uncomfortable and caused me to leave voluntarily, instead of the fact that i was directly threatened and feared for the safety of my body and spirit.] РЮц№ИЈ3. my door is not open to you, and i say this with love. i am not a trauma informed professional. if you bring me your trauma, i can relate, and i can share #hugs and tea. i can answer questions about hopeworks and give you other potential healing resources. i do not have the emotional space, training, or resources to heal you myself. this is an important distinction that is central to my own healing, and to your healing as well. 
safe journeys and much love to everyone. РЮц№ИЈ #consent #loveyourself #boundaries

text:
join the creatress @sunsetkava for our sexual healing support group & workshop. this workshop is for women and men who need a safe space & support to heal from their experiences with sexual abuse. we understand that it can be uncomfortable, even terrifying to face our past experiences with sexual abuse. we are here to support you through that fear, anxiety, discomfort, sadness, anger, and anything else that comes up as you take this incredibly brave step toward your healing. the deep sense of relief from release, the empowerment from your courageousness, and the love from supportive peers can bring so much hope and healing that can change our lives in beautiful ways. 
our main objective in this workshop series is to clear the energetic and psychological imprint that sexual trauma may have left on us that affects who we are and how we function in the world. it is so important and necessary that we reclaim our power over our sexuality and over our lives now and for generations to come, so that we may operate from a place of healing rather than a place of hurt. within this safe space, you will have the option to share your experiences and insights openly, write them in your journal or simply listen and work through things internally. this is a judgment-free zone, and a space full of love and healing energy. 
in session 1 we will be:
- identifying where we are now, in terms of our coping mechanisms. how have we been dealing with our pain?
- identifying new ways we can nurture ourselves and heal our pain
- gently recalling our experiences with sexual abuse
- defining "trauma" and identifying our triggers
- practicing new ways to respond to triggers
- identifying our strengths - identifying our support team

tweet_full:
join the creatress @sunsetkava for our sexual healing support group & workshop. this workshop is for women and men who need a safe space & support to heal from their experiences with sexual abuse. we understand that it can be uncomfortable, even terrifying to face our past experiences with sexual abuse. we are here to support you through that fear, anxiety, discomfort, sadness, anger, and anything else that comes up as you take this incredibly brave step toward your healing. the deep sense of relief from release, the empowerment from your courageousness, and the love from supportive peers can bring so much hope and healing that can change our lives in beautiful ways. 
our main objective in this workshop series is to clear the energetic and psychological imprint that sexual trauma may have left on us that affects who we are and how we function in the world. it is so important and necessary that we reclaim our power over our sexuality and over our lives now and for generations to come, so that we may operate from a place of healing rather than a place of hurt. within this safe space, you will have the option to share your experiences and insights openly, write them in your journal or simply listen and work through things internally. this is a judgment-free zone, and a space full of love and healing energy. 
in session 1 we will be:
- identifying where we are now, in terms of our coping mechanisms. how have we been dealing with our pain?
- identifying new ways we can nurture ourselves and heal our pain
- gently recalling our experiences with sexual abuse
- defining "trauma" and identifying our triggers
- practicing new ways to respond to triggers
- identifying our strengths - identifying our support team
- beginning the process of "cord-cutting" (cutting energetic ties from our abuser)
- leading a group meditation
- leading a spiritual cleansing ritual

text:
timeРђЎs up РЈ▒
.
.
.
alicia framis Рђюgender pavillionРђЮ, located inside sala de alcal├А 31 @culturacmadrid, addresses the role women play in our contemporary society & the rise of the fourth-wave feminism; through a series of architectural spaces, interactive installations, performances, photographs & videos.
.
.
the multidisciplinary exhibition is divided into two sections: one dedicated to pieces that are related to the architectural space and how we inhabit these rooms in an established manner. for example; one night tent (2002) a reversible fabric that transforms into a camping tent that can be used to have sexual intercourse.
.
.
.
the second one is more oriented towards social activism mostly performances that integrate fashion, design and video art with a clear political statement. for example; one of my favorite pieces is РђюmamamenРђЮ (2004), a series of suits design specifically for men to carry their children to work while being able to do their daily duties. .
.
.
the costume made anti-violence clothing line is also composed by a series of gowns inscribed with black pejorative phrases used by men to discriminate women over an intense yellow fabric (frequently used to create safety vests) in order to caught the attention of the citizens when they are being attacked. the name of this clothing line Рђюanti dogРђЮ (2002), was inspired by a news framis heard of sexist & racist attacks made by a group of skinheads in berlin to series of immigrant women with trained dogs.
.
.
another interesting proposal is Рђю8 de junio, libran las modelosРђЮ (2006), a performance where naked men are walking down the runway as a metaphor of the common abuse & exploration female models have to go through. or her latest performance Рђюthe walking ceilingРђЮ(2018), an allegation to the social, labor, and politically discriminatory glass ceiling woman are still bearing until this day.
.
.
.
@aliciaframis discourse couldnРђЎt be more appropriate in a context like the one we are living today; when time has come for woman to raise their voices again -with movements like #metoo- to reclaim their rights to respectfully be treated as equals in a male dominated world. .
.
on view until january 27, 2019

text:
.
i'm not one to big myself up too much but i thought i was a very brave mama today. Рюе
some people forget, itРђЎs not that easy to let go. i donРђЎt know if people just forget that not everyone is going to parent the same.
i know many people thatРђЎs given their baby up within weeks of them being born to family members to baby sit etc, to many that havenРђЎt and their kid is 9 already. 
who are any of us to judge!
Рюе
as a kid, a little older than marley, i was sexually abused by a male family member till the age of 9 (that abuse only stopped, when i left jamaica to live in the uk. also keep in mind, thatРђЎs only 1 of 3+ times iРђЎve been sexually abused but thatРђЎs for another day).
i always feared having a kid and was determined not to have one because i knew i would be overprotective like no one has ever seen before...
Рюе
so as well having first time parents nerves, donРђЎt judge people and they way they decide to parent their own kid.
for some people like me, itРђЎs mega hard to just leave my kid with anyone. that means, even with his own grandparents.
we had a open talk today and i told them why i am the way i am and i think they understand more where i was coming from. 
slowly but surely i will start to trust those in my little circle a bit more.
but sadly itРђЎs one of the awful after affects that i have to deal with for the rest of my life. 
i may not be that mama that allows her kid to be babysit by every tom dick or harry but iРђЎm making baby steps towards the right direction.
Рюе
 i tell my story, not so i get the glory but so that others may know hope.
i know the power of sharing a story. thatРђЎs why iРђЎve shared mine too.
iРђЎm here to say, there is many people like me, sadly weРђЎre not the first to experience this and wonРђЎt be the last but importantly youРђЎre not alone on this journey.
when your ready to add your voice to this community, search out a few support groups, i recently have and though i havenРђЎt got too involved and comment a lot but it nice to be surround by others like myself.
Рюе
remember itРђЎs okay to heal at your own pace ­ЪњЎ

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateРёб was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateРёб was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: so... i normally do not РђюtalkРђЮ politics either way on fb page. however i am not shy about sharing my beliefs such as animal rights, climate control, zero waste, no plastic, being against the pipeline and the wall just to name a few. i have been labeled anywhere from an activist to a liberal yet neither are entirely true. i do not claim to be anymore that human with my own set of beliefs and values... that is why i feel very strongly to speak of this... the ruling in new york regarding late term/full term abortion makes my heart sick and my soul cry. i can not even begin to explain how much. i have always been pro choice but this crosses my moral line. as a mother who was told to choose between herself or her baby i chose my baby and we were both fine! my second child was induced neither were born under great circumstances but the circumstances donРђЎt matter the universe trusted me enough to not only bring life into this world but to protect that life with my own. it is no secret that what i believe in i am extremely passionate about... so keeping my carbon footprint small, being vegan for numerous reasons, protecting the earth and the seas, and many more all are extremely important to me, so how can i be passionate about those issues but not passionate about protecting human life? text:
i love women. i know that they are smart, talented, capable, victors, warriors, leaders and more. i've always believed that they should be discredited with opportunities simply because they're a woman. which makes me surprised that others are surprised that women can be the perpetrators of heinous acts... just like men. i remember when north carolina first made the controversial "bathroom law" and everyone was up in arms about how men would be using it to abuse women. yet in this case, which hasn't had nearly the amount of coverage it would have if the perpetrators were men, women are the abusers. if an 18 year old boy public flaunted that he was grooming a 13 year old girl for a relationship, he'd be next in line for a "surviving..." documentary. but yet ariadna's getting paid (through her social media subscribers and continued blog coverage) and her relationship is described as "goals." i believe that if we're truly gonna "treat women as equals," the we need to call women out when they do wrong, just like we do men. there's no way these two issues would have flown under the radar if r. kelly's name or chris brown's name we're attached to them and these issues font deserve to be swept under the rug now.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
d├Еj├а vu all over again? pair of vetoed #metoo proposals re-introduced in the california legislature
#
benjamin m. ebbink, of counsel with fisher phillips in sacramento (photo: courtesy photo) many legislative observers nicknamed 2018 as the Рђюyear of the #metoo movement,РђЮ as state houses across the country (including california) introduced and enacted a wave of state laws designed to combat sexual harassment in the workplace. however, if the early weeks of this year are any indication, this trend of legislative activity will continue well into 2019 and beyond. in california, a pair of proposals that were vetoed by governor jerry brown in 2018 have already been re-introduced, illustrating that newly-sworn-in governor gavin newsom will be put to an early test on #metoo-inspired legislation. previous veto of assembly bill 3081 as introduced last year, assembly bill 3081 by assemblywoman lorena gonzalez (d-san diego) would have enacted a number of far-reaching provisions related to sexual harassment. however, by the end of the legislative process the measure had been whittled down to just two major provisions. first, the bill would have imposed joint liability on employers and labor contractors (such as temporary staffing agencies) for harassment. second, ab 3081 would have enacted new anti-retaliation protections for victims of sexual harassment, and would have created a rebuttable presumption of retaliationРђд

text:
a heartbreaking look at the reality of the stigma attached to alcoholics and substance abuse in our country. 
my friends won't tell their medical professionals they are addicted to alcohol and drugs because they are treated poorly when they do. 
this means they never get the right help and the stigma continues. 
the article says that in the past they needed to wait for six months sobriety for a liver transplant. there is no medical reasons for this or evidence that it's more effective. 
additionally the standard 30 days in rehab as the gold standard is also not based on facts and evidence. 
my treatment center told me the best results are seen after 90 days of treatment and a year of meetings, therapy and continued effort. most people are not staying this long and not improving in the long term. then they relapse and treatment is seen as a failure when it's not, it's being implemented incorrectly 
we are in an epidemic of substance abuse that includes alcohol yet we continue to hurt the ones suffering the most and they know it. 
we all know that everyone else loves drinking and doesn't want to stop. that's fine, no one cares about your drinking but the defensive attitudes and beliefs of alcoholism have to end of more and more of our friends, family members and children will die. 
i can't comprehend the attitude of being mean to people who are struggling with addiction.  they are in massive massive massive amounts of pain and the medical community is far behind the times. they seem to be unable to comprehend that addiction is rooted in pain and trauma and everyone deserves medical care of the highest quality, not just the rich, insured and non addicted. 
when you have alcoholism or substance abuse issues even your money can't break the stigma, it's impossible. i am well educated, professional and intelligent but when i say i am a recovering alcoholic i am immediately judged by it for the rest of my life. it's so incredibly heartbreaking ­Ъњћ link in bio!

text:
when our minds go into a place of anxiety, avoidance, or urges for negative coping skills it is trying to protect us. 
chances are, your brain has been taught to not feel certain emotions and is aware of what experiences or conversations evoke those emotions. .
so it does everything it can to help you. .
today, i challenge you to say thank you, mind, for trying to protect me. .
.
. . .

text:
on today's episode of this month's series, "when life doesn't turn out as expected," i talk about when someone intentionally hurts you. especially when the harm they cause on purpose had life-altering impacts.РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
someone cheating on you. someone spreading lies about you. someone manipulating you. there are so many different types of abuse . . . emotional, physical, spiritual, mental, sexual abuse, financial, and many more. РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
dealing with our thoughts and feelings about the person who intentionally harmed us is an important part of our healing process. РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
i know this because i've lived this. trying to come to grips with the fact that a man was capable of raping me was part of my healing process.РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
i was aware of horrible things people do in this world, but it is a completely different level when it happens to you.РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
on today's episode, i share what my journey has looked like in processing my thoughts and emotions towards the man who intentionally hurt me and changed my life forever. РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
for those who are survivors of sexual trauma, i do share some things about when i was raped by a massage therapist. if you think it will be triggering for you to listen, then please don't. your self-care is the most important thing. the worksheet for this episode contains a lot of text and questions which can be of benefit for you if listening to the episode is too much.РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
you can find the worksheet by going to restoringheart.com, then follow links to the podcast and then to episode 11. you'll find a download link at the top of the show notes for this episode.РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
if you know someone who could benefit from this episode then please pass it along. РЮцРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ
РађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађРађ

wir haben unsere posts zu jill und clair gel├Хscht, nachdem uns @ninja_rookie darauf aufmerksam gemacht hat, dass wir damit zu einer verharmlosung der t├цterschaft der sch├Хpfer der beiden figuren beitragen (vielen dank nochmal f├╝rs hinweisen!). wir stimmen voll und ganz zu und m├Хchten uns entschuldigen, die beiden figuren nicht genauer und klarer eingebettet zu haben. wir stehen klar hinter den betroffenen frauen und m├Хchten keinesfalls zu einem patriachalen genie-kult, der m├цnnliche ├╝bergriffigkeit und t├цterschaft rechtfertigt, beitragen. uns ging es vor allem um die figuren und nicht darum, die filme der t├цter zu bewerben.Рађ
Рађ
jill aus dem film manhattan (1979) und clair hanks-huxtable aus der bill cosby-show (1984-1992), sind beides figuren, die von t├цtern geschaffen wurden. Рађ
Рађ
woody allen, regisseur von manhattan, wurde von seiner adoptivtochter wegen sexuellem missbrauch angezeigt und unter dubiosen umst├цnden nicht verurteilt. bill cosby ist verurteilter sexualstraft├цter wegen mehrfacher vergewaltigung und sexuellem missbrauch. die schauspielerin der clair, phylicia rashad hat sich immer hinter ihn gestellt und das leid der ├╝berlebenden verharmlost. Рађ
Рађ
das held*innenquartett, das wir vor zwei jahren auf wepsert ver├Хffentlicht haben und nun nach und nach auf instagram reposten, soll fiktionale held*innen sammeln, die uns pers├Хnlich als feminist*innen, als kinder, jugendliche und junge erwachsene positiv beeinflusst haben und uns geholfen haben, patriachale muster zu durchbrechen. dabei promoten wir aber auf gewisse weise ja auch die filme und b├╝cher in denen sie vorkommen - und damit ihre erschaffer*innen. auch in hinsicht der aktuellen r. kelly debatte fragen wir uns, inwieweit das feministisch rechtfertigbar ist.Рађ
Рађ
was meint ihr, findet ihr diese held*innen - trotz ihrer sch├Хpfer - als vorbilder nennenswert oder sollten wir sie aus solidarit├цt mit den betroffenen frauen boykottieren?Рађ
Рађ
let us know what you think!Рађ

"there are some people out there who will never understand what itРђЎs like to be a female, to be treated as an object, disposable, and used. no exaggerations. theyРђЎll never understand our daily struggles from the most mundane things like being extra wary on our walk home, to the extreme cases like rape and sexual violence.

and i hope theyРђЎll never experience what it's like, 
but i hope more people will understand."
РЎЦ№ИЈ
last week, women and men around the world marched the streets for equality. and after months of not knowing what to write, i'm finally ready with my new blog #metoo. the men and women that have come forward and spoken out over sexual abuse, violence and inequality over the last few years have filled our lives with power, inspiration and courage. their support and stories help victims, they help to heal and they help break the cycles of abuse. thank you for helping me to heal, write and fight harder. read my latest blog #metoo by clicking that link in my bio.
РГљ№ИЈ
i hope you all find some happiness, strength and courage today x......

text:
jueves de #secretosdemiequipaje 
hoy no hay tutorial ni reviews. 
hoy comparto contigo secretos de mi coraz├│n. 
@equipajedeunamujer me ha dado la oportunidad de conocer a muchas mujeres maravillosas y acercarme a algunas con qui├Еnes coincid├Г en alg├║n momento de mi vida. una de ellas me escribi├│ hace un a├▒o, se identific├│ con algo que escrib├Г y hoy d├Гa somos amigas РЮц№ИЈ. lamentablemente ambas vivimos una experiencia en com├║n. dolorosa y amarga. .
hace unos d├Гas me env├Гo este mensaje РъА№ИЈ le ped├Г permiso para publicarlo porque as├Г como ella, como yo, tristemente hay muchas y aqu├Г les respondo РгЄ№ИЈ .
querida amiga lo logr├Е! s├Г. mirarme sin odiarme. entender que no fui ni soy culpable de esta parte de mi equipaje que ocult├Е durante a├▒os por verg├╝enza. tampoco mi cuerpo. que no necesito castigarme ni da├▒arme sino cuidarme. ┬┐c├│mo lo hiciste?, me preguntas. y te pregunto yo a ti... ┬┐cu├Аntos a├▒os llevas castig├Аndote? ┬┐trat├Аndote mal? ┬┐cu├Аnto da├▒o se requiri├│ para marchitarte, para casi anular tu amor propio? 
lo que respondas no es igual al tiempo que te tomar├А mejorar, pero ser├А el primer paso de conciencia... ese paso a Рђюcambiar de chipРђЮ. te abrir├А los ojos y empezar├Аs a ser compasiva contigo misma cuando realices lo fuerte que has sido y lo injusta que eres a la vez. -
cierra los ojos y mira tu equipaje. ┬┐por cu├Аntos a├▒os has llevado esa carga? es un proceso. no ser├А de un d├Гa para otro ese click. tomar├А meses, quiz├А a├▒os. requiere de tu fortaleza y determinaci├│n, y eso ya lo tienes. haz todo lo contrario a lo que haz hecho por a├▒os. m├Гrate al espejo y menciona todas tus cualidades, aunque quieras llamarte gorda... fea...elim├Гnalo! fake it til you make it. -
m├Гrate en los ojos de los dem├Аs, de aquellos que te aman. p├Гdeles prestados sus ojos de amor, mientras los tuyos mejoran. -
-
d├Еjate notas de amor propio, todo est├А en el cerebro y necesitas a diario reprogramarlo. 
ve a terapia. busca ayuda profesional, psicol├│gica y psiqui├Аtrica si es necesario. sin pena. no est├Аs loca, est├Аs practicando el m├Аs lindo de los artes Рђюel amarteРђЮ. .

con amor, 
stef

text:
"one of my disappointments in the wake of the #metoo movement is the response of many good men shrinking back because of fear instead of courageously stepping forward to make a difference. the most popular quote of modern times is attributed to edmund burke, Рђўthe only thing necessary for evil to triumph is for good men to do nothing.РђЎ as the #metoo movement expands, the faces of men who have done great evil to women fill our news feed. what the recent gillette commercial essentially said to men, Рђўyou will either be part of the problem or part of the solution.РђЎ practically every woman i know who has made substantial strides toward healing from sexual abuse can identify a caring, strong and safe man in her life. restoration must include courageous fathers, brothers, husbands, counselors, pastors and bosses who value women not just in word, but in actions.
.
the general response to the #metoo movement and other cultural trends has been to champion feminism and female power. what we fail to recognize is that healthy societies and families require healthy men. i am beyond grateful for the godly men in my life! men may be part of the problem, but we must also embrace that they are a critical part of the solution. may we as women never jump on the cultural bandwagon that devalues and belittles the god-given gift of authentic manhood." - dr. juli slattery
.
read more on our blog Рђюmanhood on a razorРђЎs edgeРђЮ.

text:
swipe left>>>>>>trigger warning for rape....
we have been reading and hearing a lot of comments about "false rape accusations" and how "the movement" has caused so many boys and men to be falsely accused of sexual assault. well here is the deal, false rape allegations pale in comparison to actual instances of rape, and most rapes go unreported. however, as a parent, the one thing that you can do to make the world a safer place for everyone is to teach your sons (and daughters) not to rape! teach them that going along with the crowd doesn't make them cool, it makes them weak. teach them that their actions can have a lifelong traumatic impact on a girl's life and saying i'm sorry after the fact won't fix it. teach them that verbal consent is a critical requirement for any physical interaction  and if it isn't 100% crystal clear that their partner has given consent, then it's a no. teach them that intoxicated partners can't consent. teach them that if you use threats, intimidation, force, or a weapon, that is rape. teach them early and often. please, teach them! because as you can see, kids can and do rape and molest other kids. and believe us when we say, "they're just kids" is no excuse! #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #mlk ­ЪЊИ:pixaby

text:
the other day, i accompanied a family member to a new doctor for moral support and to serve as an additional ear. wanting to be respectful, i sat in his office listening as the doctor asked the customary questions all doctors ask. what wasnРђЎt customary was the tone he was using, the abruptness, impatience, and interrupting he did as he didnРђЎt give my family member the time to gather their thoughts so they can answer accurately giving him the whole picture of why they were there asking for his help. as is my custom, i always have a small notebook with me to jot down important recommendations a doctor gives, yet, in the first 3 minutes of me sitting there i found myself writing Рђюi do not like him- he is not patient and kindРђЮ. it came to the point where i couldnРђЎt keep quiet anymore  and i respectfully requested that perhaps the doctor can rephrase the question he had asked and give my loved one an extra minute to answer. did i mention that through all this the patient was in so much physical pain that it was rated 10+ by them and the purpose of the visit was to have this doctor help manage and help treat their constant pain. 
i was raised to respect doctors and authority figures and value their skills and expertise. at the same time, i was encouraged to respectfully question when needed so that i can make informed decisions. there would have been a time when i was not much younger that i would sit in that office quietly feeling uncomfortable and angry and not say a thing- i would just take it because heРђЎs the doctor. today, i wonРђЎt and i canРђЎt keep quiet.

text:
iРђЎm very excited the share our new foundation: no silence. @_nosilence Рђб Рђюif you wait until you find something to speak up for, something that youРђЎre passionate about that concerns you and attacks your own beliefs, then eventually, when the day finally arrives, you might also find that you have forgotten how to speak.РђЮ
kamand kojouri

the purpose of no silence is essentially to serve as a platform where all the taboo related topics and heavily stigmatised topics will be addressed and discussed with the aim of debunking the unjust stigmas attached. (this will be done through a variety of mediums). i personally have touched up on and spoken about some these subjects on my social media, and the response iРђЎve received from people who could relate to the things i spoke about or have gone through similar experiences was overwhelming. all the raw stories theyРђЎve shared with me was something that truly touched me and i felt honoured that they trusted me enough to share their stories in detail with me.

iРђЎve since consistently gotten many messages and questions & i wanted to be able to lend my voice and help in any way that i can on a larger scale and platform. 
in between family, business, being a mother and simply a lot of other commitments that i have, iРђЎm glad iРђЎve been able to create the time for this as it is something dear to my heart. Рђюso, whatРђЎs next? you heal, you grow & then you help others.РђЮ

text:
@janarollerfit was sexually molested by her grandfather as a young girl. this part of her life story has had a massive impact on her life. does this resonate?
____________________________________________
when i met jana last year at the uncommon woman tour in vancouver i fell in love with her energy and her gentle soul. i always wonder how these kinds of things happen. it breaks my heart, but it also drives me deeper into my purpose to give them safe and loving platforms to be seen and heard.
____________________________________________
it has taken a lifetime of healing for jana to get to a place of loving forgiveness and peace. as she shared her story with the guests i could see the impact it had on the men and women in the audience. i could see that there were others who shared her story were holding the pain close to their hearts. janaРђЎs vulnerability and healing light gave them hope and opened them up to the grace in surrender  and the power of sharing their truth. 
____________________________________________
as women were given the mic so they could stand and share their stories and experiences with her, we could see and feel the layers of generational pain and shame begin to fall away and the healing begin. 
____________________________________________
sharing our stories saves us and saves others. i believe it with all my soul. i have witnessed it time and time again. i see it in every conversation and i saw it in every city that we stopped in during the tour. so i will continue to create these spaces for women to share, connect, heal, and be healed for as long as there are stories to share and souls to be mended. 
____________________________________________
jana is one of millions of women who have experienced sexual abuse at the hands of a loved one. in fact this kind of sexual abuse is more common than that with strangers. jana and thousands of other women are now leading the way with open conversation and their vulnerability in the hopes of igniting change, the more we educate the quicker we will eradicate the ignorance and injustices, and begin the healing process as a human collective. if you have a story you want to share, comment or dm me.

text:
do you compare yourself to others and feel less than? when we compare we are not being fair to ourselves. we usually take our negative believed thoughts and compare to othersРђЎ outward self - the self they want us to see and let us see - not the side of them with their limitations. in essence, we are comparing their highlight reel to our bloopers real - definitely not the same playing field! .

when you find that you are comparing yourself to others, are you able to identify what youРђЎre feeling?  you might be feeling a lacking of something. if you can identify what you feel is lacking, you will be able to recognize and prevent yourself from comparing. you are not less than.  stop putting yourself down. ­Ъњю

p.s.  if this is an area youРђЎd like to work on, i am taking new clients between now and february 1st.  click on the link in my bio @denisestyer to register for a complimentary call with me.  i look forward to speaking with you!

text:
i didnРђЎt notice that i felt a joy for life until i lost it. now, i yearn to reclaim it but i donРђЎt know how to. rather than passing through each day on a clear cut path, i now feel like a prisoner to life. living feels like a punishment. there is immense difficulty in mustering up enough energy to get out of bed each day - and a multitude of internal questioning of why i should. i canРђЎt shake this belief that life is too tough, too meaningless, and too painful. but i know that i once felt differently. once, there was - unbeknownst to me at the time - a subtle enjoyment of the every day which i had failed to identify and appreciate. i had taken good mental health for granted as iРђЎm sure many people with that same fortune do. those that i love and those that depend on me - plus the knowledge that i was once joyful therefore can, perhaps, be so again - are what keep me in this moment from giving up. ~coping diary
~
~

text:
"the berliner unwille #metoo", my 10th blog post since i started my blog the inbetween album last september. i thought, for the 10th one, i'd make it special. especially, since we developed the story of our shenzhen documentary, and decided to focus on children growing up in the ever-changing city, i feel that the message in this piece really does carry something special for me. it's about me and berlin, but moreover, about how i'd like to see children, my own or not, grow up in the future. to that vision, i hope to contribute however little capacity i have, by sharing my own stories, by making documentaries, and hopefully much more. (to read the blog lost: link in profile)

special thanks to the photographer, mona singh (@monasinghphotography) as always. you rock. 
and to my writing partner ripu (@ripu.d.singh.77) who keeps encouraging me to be truer to myself as i write.

text:
#tbt to my design roots. #fanart. yup, you heard right. when i was just an awkward teen (as opposed to an awkward adult) i taught myself how to design on the computer. holla to everyone who remembers paintshop pro! yes, this graphic is like...almost 20 years old.
.

seriously, though...i had major isolation issues in high school. with a couple of major traumas under my belt by 15, combined with a less-than-ideal home-life...it could have been a recipe for disaster. and although isolation wasn't the best situation, that's where i found my groove. i spent hours writing, drawing...i learned how to design and manipulate photographs. i researched and devoured all things digital art. totally #humblebeginnings
.
.
good job, young me. you made something out of those lemons, after all РЮц
.
.
.

kolejne #metoo: dzielne pi┼ѓkarki kotwicy k├│rnik ujawniaj─Ё molestowanie ich trenera, kt├│ry przez lata m├│g┼ѓ pozostawa─Є bezkarny. niekt├│re zawodniczki z tego powodu rezygnowa┼ѓy ze sportu, odchodzi┼ѓy, przerywa┼ѓy karier─Ў. nie czu┼ѓy si─Ў bezpiecznie. gdy zacz─Ў┼ѓy si─Ў tym ze sob─Ё dzieli─Є, zobaczy┼ѓy, ┼╝e zachowanie trenera by┼ѓo powszechne. uda┼ѓo im si─Ў doprowadzi─Є do jego zwolnienia. od dzia┼ѓaczy us┼ѓysza┼ѓy wtedy, ┼╝e nigdy im tego nie zapomn─Ё. gdy opowiedzia┼ѓy o tym w mediach, zarz─Ёd ich klubu wystosowa┼ѓ skandaliczny komunikat, w kt├│rym pisze o braku dowod├│w i wyrzuca kobietom, ┼╝e nie zg┼ѓosi┼ѓy im tego wcze┼Џniej, a wszystko odbywa┼ѓo si─Ў w mediach spo┼ѓeczno┼Џciowych. zastanawia si─Ў te┼╝, dlaczego pi┼ѓkarki odwa┼╝y┼ѓy si─Ў to nag┼ѓo┼Џni─Є dopiero po tym, jak zarz─Ёd zdecydowa┼ѓ si─Ў wycofa─Є dru┼╝yn─Ў z rozgrywek. nie zastanawia si─Ў, dlaczego ujawnione molestowanie mog┼ѓo pozostawa─Є bezkarne i jak to wp┼ѓywa┼ѓo na pi┼ѓkarki.

to jest kultura gwa┼ѓtu: wi─Ўkszym problemem okaza┼ѓ si─Ў moment, miejsce i spos├│b, w jaki kobiety ujawni┼ѓy przemoc, ni┼╝ sama przemoc. to ujawniaj─Ёce okazuj─Ё si─Ў winne, bo przerwa┼ѓy milczenie. s┼ѓowa kilku kobiet to nie wystarczaj─Ёce dowody dla zarz─Ёdu klubu, kt├│ry powinien dba─Є o ich komfort i bezpiecze┼ёstwo. wr─Ўcz przeciwnie - zarz─Ёd odbiera to jako bezpo┼Џredni atak na klub. nie odbiera tak za to ujawnionego seksistowskiego zachowania trenera, przez kt├│re klub traci┼ѓ kolejne pi┼ѓkarki. panowie stan─Ўli po stronie kolegi.

nigdy wam tego nie zapomnimy. nigdy nie zapomnimy przyzwolenia na seksizm i przymykania oczu na krzywd─Ў kobiet. nigdy nie zapomnimy stawania po stronie molestuj─Ёcych.

my wiemy, po kt├│rej stronie stan─Ё─Є. dzi─Ўkuj─Ў wszystkim pi┼ѓkarkom, kt├│re przerwa┼ѓy milczenie - dajecie moc nam wszystkim РЮц to nasza wsp├│lna walka, nie jeste┼Џcie i nigdy nie b─Ўdziecie w niej same Рюі­ЪЈЙ za @a_rozynska : gramy do jednej bramki!

text:
i have a story for you. i've been waiting a month to eat at this pop-up cookie shop that will finally open up after being hyped up for so long. for the past month, i've been dreaming about this cookie place, dreaming about how good and soft it would taste in my mouth, dreaming about all the love and happiness it'll finally bring me once i get to have a piece of it. i swore it was the key to my sweet tooth happiness. this cookie shop had to be the one. the best in bangkok or so i imagined. -
­ЪњЋ­ЪЇф­ЪњЋ
-
well first, let's rewind a bit. last week when i was out (looking for a random cookie), i came across this brownie place while walking. i wasn't even looking for a brownie! who cares about brownies??? jk hahaha! i do. well anyways, the lady gave me a sample of it and it was the best brownie sample of my life. damn it was just so good! so you know what i did? i bought that brownie and i ate all of it lol! well after i had my moment with the amazing brownie, i kept thinking about the damn cookie i didnРђЎt get to have yet! i kept thinking to myself, damn this brownie was definitely the best brownie i've ever had but that cookie i've been waiting for so long to have, i just can't stop thinking about it! i told myself, that cookie has to be better than this brownie. i would be settling for sure if i just kept my options limited to this brownie. hahaha. oh...the human mind. -

text:
mehr als gespannt habe ich letzte woche die kurzgeschichte #catperson, nach welcher der erz├цhlband von #kristenroupenian benannt ist, begonnen. doch schon nach ein bis zwei seiten kamen mir die s├цtze bekannt vor, noch eine seite weiter wusste ich, diese geschichte hast du schon gelesen. ich war also, ohne mich daran zu erinnern, eine von 2,6 millionen (!) leserinnen des ersten literarischen viralhypes. cat person, zuerst ende 2017 im new yorker ver├Хffentlicht, faszinierte und polarisierte, und traf genau den nerv der zeit. millenials konnten sich sofort in die feinheiten des heutigen datings einf├╝hlen (chats!), freundinnen schickten sie sich per mail, in foren wurde die schuldfrage hei├Ъ diskutiert. roupenian hat in einer auf den ersten blick simplen geschichte auf den punkt gebracht, was uns im jahr 2018 besch├цftigt hat wie nie zuvor. wann ist sex einvernehmlich? braucht es ein klares ja beiderseits, oder reicht kein nein? .
.
knapp zusammengefasst geht es in cat person um eine junge studentin, die einen etwas ├цlteren mann kennenlernt, ├╝ber wochen per chat mit ihm flirtet, und am ende eines dates mit ihm schl├цft, ohne es zu wollen. in zeiten von #metoo beschuldigt roupenian nicht, sondern zeigt die miniambivalenzen von mann-frau beziehungen und die unterschiedlichen formen, in denen sich macht zeigen und verschieben kann.
.
auch in den anderen elf geschichten geht es um m├цnner, frauen, sex, liebe und macht. einige sind gro├Ъartig (look at your game, girl; ein netter typ; der junge im pool; matchbox sign; bei├Ъerin), andere erscheinen nicht fertig durchdacht, oder sind so grausam, dass sie schwer zu ertragen sind. durch alle scheint jedoch ein unglaubliches talent von roupenian, das unaussprechliche im menschen - perversit├цten, ├цngste, machtmissbrauch und psychologische tiefpunkte - und die kultur unserer zeit einzufangen. nie findet sich ein eindeutiges narrativ, sondern sehr feine, zum teil komische und b├Хse beobachtungen. klare leseempfehlung! 
p.s. hut ab an @friederikeschilbach und @zoras_daughter f├╝r die gelungene ├╝bersetzung dieser doch sehr in der amerikanischen kultur und sprache angesiedelten geschichten.

text:
step 6 of our #16stepprogram - on how boys and men can step up and take action for #metoo.

learn to read micro-behaviours and signs of distress

in the larger context of violence against women and girls, we end up talking about issues like assault after the victim/survivor has taken the courage to share. learn to read micro-behaviours or how someoneРђЎs behaviour is changing around you. the key is to notice changes in body language, patterns like absenteeism or irregularity of any kind, physical health issues, sudden reclusiveness or anger. do not ignore these or any other signs of distress.

text:
this poetry collection was purchased from the wonderful 'poetry bookshop' in haye-on-wye (a must-visit for poetry fans). #metoo: a women's poetry anthology is not an easy-going read but a powerful and important one. emotive, potent and varied; the poets featured in this collection walk us through their many different yet similar experiences of sexual harassment, violence, assault and abuse.

i think this collection is a cathartic read for women who have gone through any of these experiences because you can see that you are not alone (which i think is one of the main motives/benefits of the #metoo movement). i would however advise against reading it if these experiences are fresh. i also think it's an important read for those who are lucky enough to have not experienced anything like the content of the collection because it will help you to understand the #metoo movement better.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text: ­Ъќц i saw lots of posts regarding the #10yearschallenge and i think itРђЎs a good idea to reflect from time to time on what has happened in the last years - not in terms of appearance, but in terms of personal growth. i believe the more you grow personally, the more you can make an impact in this world. on the left side (10 years ago - recently turned 22) i donРђЎt recognize myself. i see someone who is distant from herself and her intuition, unhappy, mentally and physically unhealthy. it took a long turbulent journey to get closer to my true self and this journey isnРђЎt over. for me personally, becoming vegan was an important part of this journey. it made my body healthy and made me question my own behavior and the disastrous behavior of humans towards each other, the animals, the planet and themselves. violence and cruelty is something that i donРђЎt want to support in any way since i have experienced it myself. itРђЎs painful to admit your mistakes and take back responsibility for your life and your actions, but itРђЎs the only way to healing. itРђЎs an amazing opportunity to be the person that you want to be. i feel endless admiration for all the kind people who take on this difficult journey of self-reflection, who battle their traumas every day, who ask questions, who never let go of their empathy and sensitivity despite of all the obstacles that society puts in their way. and please donРђЎt be so hard on yourself, you are strong and inspirational! text: for the last two days i have been working on this new art piece for my big exhibition, coming up in denmark. i love how the woman is coming to life, showing me the path. for the first time in ten years, i am using acrylics - no oil so far. i must say i am totally falling in love with acrylics! i am starting out with old holland acrylic paint, because i have adored old holland oil for a very long  time. but i might just finish up with a couple of layers of oil. the lady in red will tell me. :-) i am also using amsterdam expert and other really nice brands. if you have any suggestions on a good retarder and acrylics, feel free to share. my paintings in process, however, are going to have to rest until next week. the rest of this week, i am working on my new tv project at #tv2norge and also on my public speakings for @athenas_foredrag.

text:
when you feel that darkness creeping over your heart take a walk.
breathe in through your lungs and imagine yourself drowning.
look through your eyes and imagine you are blind.
hear with your ear and imagine you are deaf.
feel with your hands and imagine you cannot.

no matter what it is we will have something to be blessed for. 
never forget that. (some people may have lost some of the above... it doesn't matter be grateful for what you do have)

i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateРёб was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnnРђЎs don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analyticaРђЎs parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from koganРђЎs app may not have been completely deleted. koganРђЎs app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaignРђЎs use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of peopleРђЎs profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there Рђюcould have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheatingРђЮ. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesdayРђЎs hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking Рђўugh. totally uglyРђЎ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itРђЎs worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donРђЎt necessarily know itРђЎs being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itРђЎs worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youРђЎre doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleРђЎs personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnРђЎt have seen, and couldnРђЎt have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, Рђюwould work for anyoneРђЮ. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyРђЎre mercenaries. theyРђЎll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itРђЎs an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing РђЊ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public РђЊ our intimate family connections, our РђюlikesРђЮ, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatРђЎs expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text:
once in a lifetime you meet someone who changes the course of your life forever. i found my man. i approached mr. gerard to apologize to him after i placed myself at his studios at a protest on january 12, 2019 sponsored by the asheville survivors coalition. it didnРђЎt take me long to see something was terribly wrong with this group and as i began reading all the РђюvictimsРђЮ statements, i knew this man was no #rapist or #criminal. actually, he is quite the opposite. 
when i apologized to mr. gerard, he invited me to his studio and allowed me to interview him for my #college papers. i had never been in any artists studios in my entire life. his studio is the most #magical place i have ever been. he is the most warm, loving man i have ever encountered. i completely get why women love him so much. he made me feel special, he made me feel smart and most importantly he treated me with a #respect i have never felt. that is not Рђюgrooming.РђЮ that is a decent human who genuinely cares about other humans. he has allowed the abuse to continue locally because as a vet he believes in #freedomofspeech even if itРђЎs #defamatory. he is also one of the most #patriotic #veterans i have ever met. his life is the #immigrants #americandream. 
sadly for mr. gerard, despite the upstanding life he has lived he has became the target of a hate group that seems to have formed to terrorize him. this group actively recruits victims of domestic abuse and sexual assaults, grooms them and misplaces their anger and aggression at mr. gerard and his studios. the bigger issue is these are disgruntled employees who are forming against a former employer and terrorizing him. our local police forces and county and city leaders are letting this terror group operate in our city and now even our local #ashevilleregionalairport is being threatened openly on facebook by this group and its members. i did not believe in the #himtoo movement until now. 
mr. gerard is the face of the #himtoo movement. this kind of #activism associated with #metoo is nothing but thinly veiled #workplace #violence that needs to be stopped. #asheville and #theriverartsdistrict are not safe. #believeinmen #828isgreat #believeevidence

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itРђЎs worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donРђЎt necessarily know itРђЎs being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itРђЎs worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youРђЎre doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleРђЎs personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnРђЎt have seen, and couldnРђЎt have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, Рђюwould work for anyoneРђЮ. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyРђЎre mercenaries. theyРђЎll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itРђЎs an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing РђЊ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public РђЊ our intimate family connections, our РђюlikesРђЮ, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatРђЎs expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text:
suffocation 
can suffocation work like a medicine? 
to reach out into the voids :  where breathing life isn't there
and explore and engage into conversations 
with your own thoughts - 
like those thoughts were another person and your only companion. 
those conversations neglects and wards off despair you know
what connections does your heart make? with the walls of your mind
is evolution in your reactions from panic change - 
into inquisitiveness then playfulness and later creativity 
leading you into a realm that was non existent, until -
the medicine worked its falsification on you : suffocation worked on you. 
suffocation would never walk out of your life 
unless , you realize. 
after all suffocation is just a delusion your mind temporarily created 
to protect you from harms way : so that you survive! 
poem poring out after a date with my wife in court.  thanks to indian law. 
#suffocation #poems #medicine #falsification #poetschoice #metoo #mentalharrassmentbywoman
